text.text: My friend and I made an appointment to visit on a Saturday afternoon. When we arrived, we were greeted immediately. As this was our first visit, we were given a brief orientation. After ordering our drinks, we went in to meet the kitties. It was a fun hour of petting cats and swapping stories about our own pets with others. When we left, my friend and I agreed that we both felt less stressed and more relaxed than we had been. We'll definitely visit again.

Visited from Chicago and decided to stop by because who doesn't love cats and the coffee is a bonus! No, but seriously the staff was super friendly and I love that they take care of the cats. The cookie I got was really good and so was my iced chai. Pretty affordable too! The cats were all super cute and overall it was a fun experience.

A really lovely place to visit if you’re a cat person! The staff here are very friendly and attentive, both to you and the cats. It’s clear that they genuinely care about the happiness of every cat living here.

The cats are adorable, each with their own unique personality. Some are especially affectionate and will completely melt your heart!

The price is affordable—$12 includes admission and a selection of drinks, such as iced tea or coffee, at no extra cost. However, some specialty drinks require an additional fee. It would be even better if visitors could stay longer than an hour!

This makes the pricing explanation clearer and aligns with what you want to convey.

Amazing.  Clean, very well-kept,  and doesn't smell like a litter box! Lots of well-cared for, Cats and Kittens. Spoke with the owners about their experiences owning a Kitty Cafe. Seemed like genuine cat lovers with huge hearts providing the best care possible for as many cats as possible.

This was my first time there and I loved it so much.  There's a mix of kittens and older cats. Also playful and mellow.  There were some younger kids there 1-2 years and all the cats were so friendly. Highly recommend and if you're looking for a kitten or cat to give a forever home, talk to them.about adoption.  Nice selection of gifts and goodies in the store as well.

We have been several times over the summer to the new location in Lees Summit and my kids love it! We finally decided it was time to adopt and found the purrfect kittens! The staff was so friendly and helpful in answering all my questions! They have such cute toys and cat items too! I found the perfect sticker to go with our kittens!

cafes.name: Whiskers Cat Cafe & Coffeehouse
cafes.address: 3705-3707 SW Trafficway, Kansas City, MO 64111, USA

text.text: I  was visiting KC for work and wanted to do something fun in the evening. For $40 I got a painting lesson and 2 hours with the kitties! They were so obviously well cared for and loved the company! I had multiple kitties jump in my lap while painting and plenty other kitties there were begging for some playtime with the toys in the room. I had a blast, and would recommend to anyone!

I love this cafe so much. I adopted my best friend, Ringo from here a couple years ago, and I couldn't be happier with that decision knowing that they believed that I was the best fit for this sweet cat. They put so much effort and time into making sure these furbabies are taken care of through their adoption process. The atmosphere is so cozy and inviting between the cafe and the cat visiting space. The kitties clearly have plenty of enrichment and precautions are taken to make sure sicknesses doesn't spread. Also, the drinks are so good! I can't praise this place enough. You can rest at ease knowing that your money is going towards a good cause!

This was such a lovely experience. We will definitely be back. So many well taken care of babies. The atmosphere was so calming and the vibes were just amazing. Had a ball and hope to take home a baby soon. 10/10+ will be back.

I recently visited this cat cafe and had a wonderful time! I ordered a hot cocoa and a banana walnut muffin, and both were absolutely delicious. The cafe had a charming atmosphere, and the cats were adorable—especially the playful kittens. I could easily see myself coming back for another relaxing visit.

However, the only downside was that it was quite busy during my visit, and there were a few young children who seemed a bit disruptive to the cats. Some of the kids were chasing them around, which made the cats visibly distressed. One even climbed onto a table and ended up falling over, which was concerning. I feel like the cafe might be better suited for older guests who understand how to interact gently with animals. Overall, a great spot for cat lovers, but best enjoyed during quieter times!

These pictures are from my first visit :)

Cute cat Cafe near downtown Columbia! $12 for a whole hour and many cats to pet and play with. As a bonus, they are all adoptable. They also have some board games and books to read and a small cafe menu with drinks and pastries to choose from.  A great place for any cat lover to check out!

Went with some friends from over an hour away to check it out. Seemed a bit to get in and then we got a wrap which cost extra and it was a tortilla wrapped around all croutons with dressing.. the texture of cat litter to the smell of cat litter..
It was very fun to hang and interact with the stars of the show at least.

cafes.name: Whisker Station Cat Cafe and Lounge
cafes.address: 212 N Kirkwood Rd, Kirkwood, MO 63122, USA

text.text: Loved it! Went for my birthday with my husband. Pet and play with kittens and drink coffee. Really nice staff. Walk in the cat area and the cats run to you and greet you.  Very therapeutic environment. Would love to adopt through them one day ❤️🐱

This is a delightful oasis.
You don't come here for food or exquisite coffee. You come for the kitties. They bring you peace and joy, regardless of the turbulence in your life at the moment.
This is my happy place!!! The cats are all adorable and they currently have lots of adorable kittens right now to play with go check them out!!!

Saint Charles.name: Cat Zen Cafe and Lounge
Saint Charles.address: 319 N Main St, St Charles, MO 63301, USA

text.text: This place was so much fun! What a great value to get to hang out with some awesome cats! When we went, it was nine dollars per person for a half hour which is plenty of time. It feels very relaxed and Zen inside which I guess goes with the name they had gentle music playing. The cats are all relaxed, and it was overall a very chill vibe. The cats were all very sweet and willing to be petted. The lots of toys and things to use to interact with the cats it all felt extremely clean and tidy, and you could tell they put a lot of effort into making the space, welcoming and accessible for visitors. The staff was very polite and insured we had a good time. They had a restroom available, which was clean and well stocked.could use a little more seating, especially comfy chairs. Overall had a great experience and would definitely go back.

Thank you for shaping this beautiful boy into the sweet kitty he is. He fits in so perfectly with our family.  Loves cuddles all day. Has the cutest meows. I am so happy we decided to stop there that day and play with the cats because if we wouldn't have I would not have Butters"Little". My family and I could not imagine not having this boy around.

Very kind staff, amazing atmosphere, and wonderful cats. I’d highly recommend coming here! Shrimp is darling and I hope she finds a wonderful home! Of course, the same goes for all the great cats here. Also, the price for an hour is very reasonable, and if you have the time, I’d recommend it over 30 minutes since you’ll get more time with the sweet kitties here!

cafes.name: Mochas and Meows
cafes.address: 3265 Falls Pkwy V, Branson, MO 65616, USA

text.text:
We've only lived here a year and this has become a birthday tradition already. All three of my girls have requested a stop here on their birthday (and each recieved a free cat ears headband for it!). The food is even great! They really are passionate about what they do, and they only receive kitties from the Humane Society.
This place makes you want to bring all the kitties home with you!

So first of all, their smoothies are amazing. Had a Russian blue and it's probably going to be something I crave till I'm back in branson! Second, the cat room prices are so affordable as well. We met little Susan, Gravy, Frankfurt and so many other cats deserving of a family.
They had posters showing the amount of litter and pet food they used. And they had a WHOLE BOARD dedicated to showing what cats could tolerate what kind of person/home life. This place obviously cares for it's cats AND it's employees. Give it a try! You can't get an animal experience, food, and a beverage for anywhere else in branson under 40 bucks!

This place is awesome! So many kitties and great drinks too! The staff is so friendly and if you purchase a drink they had deliver it right to you so you can keep playing with the cats! Very happy this place exists. If you need a pick me up, definitely visit here

cafes.name: The Cheshire Grin Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 1926 Cherokee St, St. Louis, MO 63118, USA

text.text: Very nice place. They genuinely want their cats to have the best chance of finding a forever home. When I was there they had a conversation about taking a cat younger than 6 months home with a friend so they can be socialized properly. They make very good drinks  and have some cute merch. As a nonprofit it goes back to taking care of the kitties.

What a place! We weren't really sure what to expect when we went. My wife and I had tried another cat cafe months ago, but decided to go to Cheshire Grin with the kids due to the reasonable prices and great amenities and reviews. We weren't as familiar with the area, but were ready for an adventure.

Y'all....THIS is the one. This is the cat cafe to visit. The staff were patient and helpful, the cafe itself spans TWO floors of a classic building, now outfitted for maximum cat enjoyment. There were a wide variety of cat ages and cat temperaments - something for everyone. Nice food and drink options (but no pressure), cool info on each cat, board games aplenty for cat-adjacent hangouts....

Plus...it's somehow LESS of a cost compared to others in the area? HOW?!

We've made our decision, and our family will be heading back to Cheshire Grin soon. Highly recommended!!

this is one of my favorite places in st. louis!! the cats seem so happy, and it’s always nice to hang out with them. we adopted our little guy from here a year ago and they made the process super easy for us. plus, the coffee is great :)

cafes.name: Zoomies Pet Cafe + Boutique
cafes.address: 5838 Macklind Ave, St. Louis, MO 63109, USA

text.text:
This is an adorable pet cafe. Lots of space. Great coffee. Shop with lots of gifts for pet lovers. I highly recommend.
They rent this space which is in an older city building so they were working on the heat and plumbing. Attentive and kind staff.

Amazing. Wish we lived closer. Our very spoiled pup got a bone broth flight! The yard was great even though we came on a chilly 🥶 day.

For us the coffee and egg bites were excellent!

Great place for food and coffee! The outdoor dog space and patio is really nice, as well as the indoor space. The only downside of our visit was that there were so many unleashed large dogs inside that it made it difficult to eat and a small fight broke out with the dogs.
I wish the staff would enforce the leashed dog rule inside that is posted several places, but they don’t.

cafes.name: Cat's Meow, Inc
cafes.address: 2600 S 11th St, St. Louis, MO 63118, USA

text.text: Bartender was super rude we ended up walking out and not ordering because of how rude she was. I think it was because we were a lot younger than the usual crowd in there. I’ll take my money to big daddies down the street then.
Wild turkey 101 is the best here. This bar sells smokes, how convenient. Came here for a late night drink, since eat crow closed over an hour early we came here.
What a place!!! I love these type joints..cash only..locals...cold cold beer...parking on the street..amazing neighborhood spot. Well done guys!!

cafes.name: Baristocats Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 702 E McCarty St, Jefferson City, MO 65101, USA

text.text:
These poor cats. The stench is awful and the people are rude. There is no cafe anything. You can pay $5 for a tiny cup of maxwell house but that is all thats available.
Wife and I tried to adopt a cat. We were ignored for weeks. Could never get a response.
The volunteers were rude when we went in, they made it very uncomfortable.
We ended up going to the shelter to adopt our cat.

This cafe is amazing and so comfortable the kittens and adult cats are adorable, loving, & playful. The service i received was nice and down to earth and the coffee was good I would most definitely come back here anytime!

The coffee is fine, but the thing is - you don't go there for the coffee or snacks - you go there for the CATS. They provide a wide variety of enrichment for the cats, and lots of comfortable places to sit and wait for a kitty to come see you. Want to play? There are a ton of toys to use to engage the cats. The Cafe provides a safe place where you can really get an idea of each cat's personality. I love taking my daughter there!

cafes.name: Sugar Kittens Lees Summit
cafes.address: 294 SW Blue Pkwy, Lee's Summit, MO 64063, USA

text.text: I went to Sugar Kittens lees summit with my mom today!! I have to say that it was amazing. The place was clean, the workers were very kind, and it was a calming environment. All the cats there are very precious and cute! I highly recommend you going here especially if you have a cat obsession! You don’t even need a reservation but you can get one.
I took my daughter Sugar Kittens in Lee’s Summit and we loved it. The place was so clean and the kittens were so cute. Very peaceful and relaxing environment. We will definitely be back!!!

I adopted a kitten from the Liberty location and checked out the new Lees Summit one and it was a great experience! So many kitties, very clean, and staff all very nice and helpful. I ended up adopting a kitten at my visit a couple of weeks ago and the process was so easy. Would highly recommend if you are looking to adopt or even just hangout with some kitties!

cafes.name: Kittens & Kuddles
cafes.address: 1000 Warrenton Shoppes Suite 23, Warrenton, MO 63383, USA

text.text: We celebrated my birthday there. They were very accommodating for a small group. The party room was nice and they furnished the plates, napkins, plasticware and simple decorations.  My mother loves cats, so this was a great place for her. We did cake first and then went out to the lounge to play with the cats.
Amazing place to bring your kids. Cats are so cuddly and playful. I would recommend. Make sure to ask about adopting one!

My friend took me here to celebrate my birthday and it was wonderful. The staff were very friendly and the kitties were so much fun to play with. The room was large, there was plenty of places to sit and LOTS of toys to play with. I can't wait to come back 🥰

Olathe.name: Second Cup Cat Cafe
Olathe.address: 417 N Rawhide Suite F, Olathe, KS 66061, USA

text.text: I absolutely adore this place and Melissa who runs it. I run a small rural rescue and as such sometimes struggle to find adoptions quick enough. They take good care of the animals and are always quick to tell me if I need to bring one of mine back to the shelter for whatever reason. Our kitties love the room to run and play. We have been a shelter partner for a year now and adopted our over 60. We couldn't do it without them!

booked a reservation for my mom and i here at the second cup cat cafe today and we both loved our visit! we weren’t expecting to have the entire room full of cats for ourselves for an hour, so the calm and quiet atmosphere with cats everywhere was very therapeutic for the both of us. all of the cats were some of the friendliest and most playful that i have met, in addition to being very well taken care of and loved with plenty of space, toys, and mental stimulation at their disposal. will definitely be coming back here and would recommend stopping by if you are in the area 😊

What a fun, unique experience . We were there on a bingo night and played for prizes. All the money raised went to support the adoptable cats. All the snacks and drinks were free. The cats are all free to roam about the room and interact with everyone there, hoping to find a forever home.

cafes.name: Blue Cat Lounge At Alhonna Resort
cafes.address: 677 Outer Dr, Lake Ozark, MO 65049, USA

text.text: On vacation for the wknd, we stopped in before noon to see the famous “Ozarks” sign and had a drink and the nachos. Nachos were SO good! It was after the busy season so pool was closed and low traffic, but a nice view and friendly service!
Stayed during off season while the snow fell. Talk about beautiful!!! So friendly! We enjoyed the comfortable spot we had. The fishing areas is convenient and easy to get to! FISH ON good food

This place is amazing. I enjoyed the food. The jukebox plays the same song over and over by an employee named Tuck. My uncles got electrocuted on the dock and I found 50 million dollars inside the walls of my cabin, which by the way was fully renovated. HAHAH. All jokes aside. I LOVE THIS PLACE

We’ve been talking about adopting a cat for over a year and remembered that Espurresso was a cozy place that provided interactive sessions with cats. We decided we would only adopt if we really connected with a cat. Brittany was a very knowledgeable and helpful barista and answered all of our questions. We got to spend quality time with the cats and ended up adopting Starlight! There was a good assortment of cats, but Starlight is the perfect cat for us. We’ve renamed her Mocha and she’s adjusting well. We look forward to providing a safe and happy forever home for her 🖤

Such a wonderful place! I was in town for my birthday, thought how lovely it would be to see some new kitties, and took a chance to go in without a reservation.

The person at the counter was very kind. They answered my questions, got me setup for the next slot, and recommended a refreshing drink while I waited. There a purrfect photo moment wall, and some lovely cat-related books to browse and relax with.

The ambience was clean and cute. The community fliers made me feel included and welcome. And of course, the kitties!! I had been following them on social media for awhile so it was great to see firsthand the love and attention that goes into socializing these kitties and getting them to their next homes. Thank you to everyone involved in this special place!

This is one of my favorite places here in Lawrence. As someone who has always loved cats, having a little cafe on Mass street dedicated to delicious treats and adorable adoptable kitties is like a dream come true. I know several people who have adopted their kitties through the cafe and have had an amazing experience. These kitties get shown in a new light when they aren’t in a cage at a shelter. Their personality really shines through!

The cats and the treats aren’t the only good thing. I’ve had great encounters with both owners who are just amazing! Brittanie, one of the owners, knows myself and the little boy I nanny by name and is just so personable. They’ll always make you feel right at home!

Thank you Espurresso for all that you do for us customers and the sweet kitties that come through the Cafe.

cafes.name: Lucky cat
cafes.address: 533 E Elm St, Republic, MO 65738, USA

text.text: They have options for sweetness. I usually find things too sweet, so this is one of the few places I frequent.
The food is good the people are so kind the atmosphere is calm a pretty
One of my favorite places to go!

cafes.name: Republic - Lucky Cat Boba Tea and Sweets
cafes.address: 558 E Harrison St, Republic, MO 65738, USA

text.text: What a nice change for the town of Republic! Boba is definitely on the rise around this area and more and more spots were popping up, but in Springfield. So with this location being in Republic and in a very accessible location, the only thing left was to go and try it for myself, I can truly say I was very pleased with the whole service and the product that they were putting out to the other customers and myself

I usually really love this place. We live about 30 minutes away so it's a nice little treat when we come into town. I always get the chai milk tea with tapioca pearls. Well, this morning I didn't start drinking it til we were almost home. There was something off about it, couldn't figure it out. Got home and opened it and there's no milk in it. It's not going to stop me from coming here, just going to make sure I check my drinks before I leave from now on.
Best boba around!! I used to drive 25 minutes to their Springfield location. Very happy to have them closer. Good vibes and neat items in their shop.

cafes.name: Lucky Cat Boba Tea and Taiyaki
cafes.address: 3480-3450 S Stewart Ave, Springfield, MO 65804, USA

text.text: As an anime fan, this store is one of my favorites. Not only does it have a lot of anime peripherals, but it also has a lot of delicious food. I like the ice cream very much, and the other milk teas are also delicious.

Every time I get my hair done or go to Joann’s I always come by to get a treat and the boba is always good and the service is always so sweet and nice (even when I come in with foils still in)! Excited to try to new location soon
Pretty ok boba shop, was cute and boba drinks were ok. Not what I usually get but was something different.
